* KeyValue Redesign
   - Discard current 'updates' mechanism
   - Each store tracks a series of (key,value,revision,timestamp)
       - Appends just add to the end
   - Stores are only required to store latest entry for a key
   - Reads return only the last value for each key
   
   - Reads must achieve threshold on each KV pair independently
   - Deletions are unrecoverable threshold failures
   
   - For apps that overwrite multiple keys, can save space by sharing (revision,timestamp)
      - Similar to current 'update' scheme
      
   - There will be no need to "compact" KV objects. Each store can do that locally.
      - For now we'll load the whole KV object
      
